OL,3,CMan confined girlfriend to bedroom
OL,4,Cwithout food and drink for four days
OL,6,FThe woman fled from the bedroom into
OL,7,Fthe kitchen and asked a neighbour to
OL,8,Fcall the police.
OL,10,FPower later admitted using controlling
OL,11,Fand coercive behaviour as well as
OL,12,Fintimidating her as a witness.
OL,14,FHe was jailed for two years and 10
OL,15,Fmonths and given a 10-year restraining
OL,16,Forder
OL,18,FDeputy circuit judge Timothy Clayson
OL,19,Fsaid his impact on the victim had been
OL,20,F"substantial".
